
Filters and Redirections
------------------------

Filters : Commands that process data (input -> output)

Examples
grep   =  Find text
sort   =  Arrange data
uniq   =  remove duplicates

Redirection

Controls where input/output goes 
Instead of just printing on screen
. Save to file
. Append to file
. Pass to another file


Core Idea 
Command -> Output  -> (Redirect or filter) -> Result

Part 1 : Redirection

(>)  -> Overwrite output
Send output to a file (and replace existing content)

   ls -l > test.txt

Use case:
. Save logs 
. Store command output

Notes : If the file exists -> It will be overwritten

(>>)  -> Append output
Adds output to the end of the file (does not overwrite)
  
    echo "Hello" >> file.txt

Use case:
. Appending data


(<)  -> Input Redirection
Takes input from the file instead of keyboard

    cat < file.txt   Same as   cat file.txt

Use case
. Feeding input scripts


(|)  -> Pass output of one command as input to another 

   cat file.txt | grep error

Use case:
. Log filtering


Part 2 : Filters

Cat   -> view file
  cat file.txt

grep  -> Search text
   grep "error" file.txt  

sort  -> Sort lines alphabatically
   sort file.txt

uniq  -> Remove duplicates lines (only consecutive)
    uniq file.txt

wc   -> Word count
    wc -l file.txt (counts lines)
